ting for me because i'm black. or maybe others who are just inspired by the idea of breaking new ground. and so i think all that's a wash. the bottom line is am i viewed as somebody who's gonna be a champion for the guy who's waking up every day, working hard for a paycheck? and i'm confident that if they think i can help them, that i've got a shot at getting their vote. and it may take a little more work on my part. but i don't mind working harder than the other guy.</p></span>



